title: Google\Cloud\WebSecurityScanner\V1beta\Finding
name: Finding
description:
A Finding resource represents a vulnerability instance identified during a ScanRun.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.websecurityscanner.v1beta.Finding

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The resource name of the Finding. The name follows the format of 'projects/{projectId}/scanConfigs/{scanConfigId}/scanruns/{scanRunId}/findings/{findingId}'. The finding IDs are generated by the system.

params.name: data.finding_type
params.description: The type of the Finding. Detailed and up-to-date information on findings can be found here: https://cloud.google.com/security-scanner/docs/scan-result-details

params.name: data.http_method
params.description: The http method of the request that triggered the vulnerability, in uppercase.

params.name: data.fuzzed_url
params.description: The URL produced by the server-side fuzzer and used in the request that triggered the vulnerability.

params.name: data.body
params.description: The body of the request that triggered the vulnerability.

params.name: data.description
params.description: The description of the vulnerability.

params.name: data.reproduction_url
params.description: The URL containing human-readable payload that user can leverage to reproduce the vulnerability.

params.name: data.frame_url
params.description: If the vulnerability was originated from nested IFrame, the immediate parent IFrame is reported.

params.name: data.final_url
params.description: The URL where the browser lands when the vulnerability is detected.

params.name: data.tracking_id
params.description: The tracking ID uniquely identifies a vulnerability instance across multiple ScanRuns.

params.name: data.form
params.description: An addon containing information reported for a vulnerability with an HTML form, if any.

params.name: data.outdated_library
params.description: An addon containing information about outdated libraries.

params.name: data.violating_resource
params.description: An addon containing detailed information regarding any resource causing the vulnerability such as JavaScript sources, image, audio files, etc.

params.name: data.vulnerable_headers
params.description: An addon containing information about vulnerable or missing HTTP headers.

params.name: data.vulnerable_parameters
params.description: An addon containing information about request parameters which were found to be vulnerable.

params.name: data.xss
params.description: An addon containing information reported for an XSS, if any.
